Open Cloud HTTP Resource Adaptor and Examples

HTTP Examples Quick Start
------------------------

This file summarises the steps required to get the example HTTP services
deployed in your SLEE.

QUICK START:

0. Start your SLEE - $RHINO_HOME/start-rhino.sh

1. Edit http.address and http.port properties in build.properties

These properties specify the IP address and port that the HTTP RA will
attempt to listen on when it is activated. The defaults are 0.0.0.0 (ie.
all interfaces) and port 8000. Edit these properties if necessary for
your environment. Ensure that client.home points to your Rhino
client directory, eg. /home/user/rhino/client.

2. Deploy the examples

Using Ant, build the "deployexamples" target. This will deploy the HTTP
resource adaptor and the example HTTP service.

$ ant deployexamples

3. Use an HTTP client to test

Using any browser you should be able to go to http://<rhinohost>:8000
and see a simple test page generated by the HTTP Ping SBB.

4. The command line options available for switchsim.sh are:
Available command line format:
        -r <argument> : Request rate (default: 1.0 requests/second)
        -s            : Start sending messages immediately
        -g            : Start GUI
        -y <argument> : Ramp up time (s)
        -u <argument> : URL to request (required)
        -m <argument> : Method (default: GET)
        -c <argument> : Maximum number of HTTP connections (default: 20)
        -d <argument> : Maximum HTTP request pipeline depth (default: 5)
        -f <argument> : Request content file
must specify a URL using -u

(The scripts assume that Rhino and this examples package are on the
same host)
